					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Ok, I got it all working now. So by setting my header to NROM-256 (setting the number of 16kb PRG-ROM banks to $02) I'm able to run <em>rainwarrior</em>'s example no problem.<br /><br />==<br />NROM-256 example:<br />PRG size is $8000 -&gt; 32,768 bytes<br />CHR size is $2000 -&gt; 8,192 bytes<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; start&nbsp; end&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; size<br />PRG - $8000, $FFFF -&gt; $8000 (ro)<br />CHR - $0000, $1FFF -&gt; $2000 (ro)<br /></div><br /><br />==<br />NROM-128 example:<br />ROM7 size is $4000 -&gt; 16,384 bytes<br />CHR ROM space -&gt; (not sure where)<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;start&nbsp; end&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; size<br />ROM7 - $C000, $FFFF -&gt; $4000 (ro)<br /></div><br /><br />This is good because now I have a choice between 128 and 256 NROM, which I was vaguely aware of before. What are the advantages of having less PRG ROM? Is it a trade off for having more memory for say graphics/music?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

