				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">StephenM wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What are the advantages of having less PRG ROM? Is it a trade off for having more memory for say graphics/music?</div><br />The biggest practical advantage is that a smaller ROM can help get your work onto a collaborative multicart. A 512K cart, for example, can fit 12 NROM-256 games or 20 NROM-128 games (assuming 32K menu and no CHR compression). But if you can't cut your 20K PRG ROM to 16K, don't fret just yet, as some advanced multicart engines  can compress other games' CHR data into the empty space.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

